The paper presents a segmentation method for pituitary adenoma using an algorithm developed in previous work for segmentation of glioblastoma multiforme. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of neuroimaging data, which suggests that it could belong to the neural engineering (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) data, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
